{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"12ca689f-5e3e-4cc8-9fea-1e232ae773c9","content":"Good news — **.NET 10 `dotnet test` natively speaks the MTP protocol**, so you **no longer need `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport`**. That property was the .NET 9 opt-in bridge. In .NET 10 it's the default behavior.\n\nYou only need to keep `EnableMSTestRunner` (which makes MSTest produce an MTP-based executable). Here's the fix:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_IQOzLdrb5TNwtOBNtDXgOl","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Removing obsolete MTP property"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"tooluse_fWam3b4GAEwnJZ17WeXpPX","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-a1e55926480b4102bcee41c4b303e04e/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>","new_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-a1e55926480b4102bcee41c4b303e04e/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"7155363b-bd17-4743-9000-4cf607cda5e2","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is on .NET 10 SDK (10.0.100) and wants to know about native MTP support. Let me check what's new in .NET 10 regarding Microsoft.Testing.Platform.\n\nIn .NET 10, `dotnet test` has been rewritten to natively integrate with Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP). The key changes are:\n\n1. **`TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` is no longer needed** — In .NET 10, `dotnet test` natively speaks the MTP protocol. The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property was a bridge/opt-in for .NET 9 to make the old `dotnet test` work with MTP test apps. \n\n2. **`EnableMSTestRunner` or `TestingPlatformEnabled` is still required** — This property tells MSTest to generate a test executable that uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform as its runner.\n\n3. The new `dotnet test` automatically detects and communicates with MTP-based test projects using the MTP protocol by default, though you can override this with `--use-testing-platform` or `--use-vstest` flags if needed.\n\nSo the recommendation is to remove `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` since it's no longer necessary on .NET 10, but keep the property that enables MTP in your test framework.","outputTokens":698,"requestId":"286F:8013F:1560304:16CC91F:6A04603B"},"id":"7fbea841-22d9-4305-b993-cafa72cefe1f","timestamp":"2026-05-13T11:28:19.355Z","parentId":"9b860930-fe2d-4b33-95a6-c8adc0a6363f"}
